{
  "texts": [
    "Other approaches include training multi-task models to exploit correlation among intent classification and named entity recognition tasks, like in [15] and [16].",
    "All these methodologies are based on encode-only models, whose outputs are embedding vectors containing the semantic information of the input text.The past few years have witnessed a surge in large decoder-only models, such as GPT-3 [4], LaMDA [5], PaLM [6], GPT-4 [7] and LLaMA2 [8], challenging the dominance of encoder-only architectures for Natural Language Understanding tasks.",
    "These models learn probabilistic distributions over language, allowing them to have text-generation capabilities, and enabling them to cast many traditional NLU tasks.",
    "They can directly perform tasks in zero-shot or few-shot in-context learning manner and achieve strong performance without the need for any supervised training [17].There have been initial analyses on the capabilities of large decoder-only models in NLU tasks.",
    "An analysis on the GPT series is done in [18], but encoder-only architectures are not considered."
  ]
}